The paper discusses the use of Deep Learning methods for modeling complex phenomena occurring in natural physical processes. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the use of Deep Learning methods, which falls under the Machine Learning sub-category. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of Deep Learning methods for modeling complex phenomena, which is a common application of Artificial Intelligence. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the use of Deep Learning methods, which is a subfield of Neural and Evolutionary Computing. 

cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the use of Deep Learning methods for modeling physical processes, which falls under the Computational Science sub-category. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of Deep Learning methods for modeling physical processes, which is a common application of Systems and Control.
